<h1>1. Create and Prepare an MVC Project</h1>

<p>As the first step in developing the Typing Test application, create a new MVC project and prepare the project by adding a new controller and a new view.</p>
<h3>To create a new project</h3>
<ol>
    <li>
        <p>Open <b>Visual Studio</b>. On the menu bar, click <b>File</b>, then select <b>New</b>, and then click <b>Project</b>, or, instead of this, you can create a new project by clicking <b>New Project</b> from the <b>Start</b> page.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>In the <b>New Project</b> dialog box:</p>
        <ul>
            <li>
                <p>On the left of the <b>New Project</b> dialog box select <b>Installed</b>, then click <b>Templates</b>. On the list of templates select <b>Visual C#</b>, then click <b>Web</b>. </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>In the middle of the dialog box above the list of the templates select <b>.Net Framework version 4.5</b>. Then on the list of templates, select the <b>ASP.NET Web Application</b> template. </p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>On the right of the dialog box click <b>Change Authentication</b>. Then in the <b>Change Authentication</b> box select <b>No Authentication</b>, and then click <b>OK</b>.</p>
            </li>
            <li>
                <p>Name the project <b>Typing Test</b>, choose the location to store the project. Make sure the <b>Create directory for solution</b> check box is selected, and then click <b>OK</b>.</p>
            </li>
        </ul>
    <li>
        <p>In the <b>New ASP.Net Project</b> dialog box select the <b>MVC</b> template among the <b>ASP.Net 4.5.2 Templates</b> and click <b>OK</b>.</p>
    </li>
</ol>
<p>The project has been created by default.</p>
<h3>To create a new controller</h3>
<ol>
    <li>
        <p>In <b>Solution Explorer</b>, right-click the <b>Controllers</b> folder and then click <b>Add</b>, then click <b>Controller</b>.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>In the <b>Add Scaffold</b> dialog box, click <b>MVC 5 Controller - Empty</b>, and then click <b>Add</b>.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>In the <b>Add Controller</b> dialog box specify controller name <b>TestController</b>, click <b>Add</b>.</p>
    </li>
</ol>
<p> Notice that a new file named <b>TestController</b> has been created in the <b>Controllers</b> folder, and a new folder <b>Views\Test</b> has also been created.</p>
<p>By default, the controller <code>TestController</code> consists of the one <code>Index</code> method returning the <code>Index</code> view.</p>
