<h3>To create a new view</h3>
<ol>
    <li>
        <p>In <b>Solution Explorer</b>, right-click in the body of the <code>Index</code> method within the <code>TestController</code>  class and click <b>Add View</b>.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>In the <b>Add View</b> dialog box, leave the <b>View name</b> box as the default view engine - <b>Index</b>. On the <b>Template</b> list, click <b>Empty (without model)</b>. Leave the <b>Create as a partial view</b> check box unselected. To select the value for the <b>Use a layout page</b> box, click the <b>Additionally</b> button <img id="buttonImage" src="~/Content/Tutorial/4.png" alt="The 'Additionally' button" />.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>On the list of the project folders, select the <b>Views/Shared</b> folder. In the <b>Contents of folder</b> select <b>_Layout.cshtml</b>. Press <b>OK</b>.</p>
    </li>
    <li>
        <p>In the <b>Add View</b> dialog box, click <b>Add</b>.</p>
    </li>
</ol>
<p>The <b>_Layout.cshtml</b> file is a template for views. It allows you to specify the HTML container layout in one place and then apply it across multiple pages on your site. It is also used to add separate files to the project, for example <b>CSS</b> files of styles, <b>JavaScript</b> files and other content types that are required.</p>
